verbs.description: overextend (third-person singular simple present overextends, present participle overextending, simple past and past participle overextended)

entries.meaning: To expand or extend to an excessive degree, especially to do so beyond a safe limit.
(linguistics, transitive) To apply (a term) to too many referents, by overextension.
(chess, transitive) To push a pawn too far, so that it becomes vulnerable to the opponent's attacks.
